00:36.471 --> 00:38.081
- Well, all kids
go through phases.

00:38.125 --> 00:40.083
I'm told.

00:40.127 --> 00:41.563
Well, whatever he's
going through right now,

00:41.606 --> 00:44.305
I gotta tell you,
I'm a little over it.

00:46.133 --> 00:48.309
Maybe he just...

00:48.352 --> 00:51.051
needs some masculine energy.

00:51.094 --> 00:52.878
both: Hey!
- Home run!

00:52.922 --> 00:54.271
- Thanks, Coach!
- Boom!

00:54.315 --> 00:55.533
You wanna do it again?
- Yeah, let's do it.

00:55.577 --> 00:56.752
- All right, good job.
Let's go.

00:56.795 --> 00:58.971
- Okay.

00:59.015 --> 01:00.799
- All right, line up there.

01:00.843 --> 01:04.020
Same again, nice and easy.

01:04.064 --> 01:06.501
- Thank you.

01:06.544 --> 01:08.981
both: Mm.

01:09.025 --> 01:10.679
Home sweet home.

01:10.722 --> 01:12.550
- Mm-hmm.
- Thanks for coming with.

01:12.594 --> 01:14.900
I know my father
was happy to see you.

01:14.944 --> 01:16.554
- I love my old man-in-law.

01:16.598 --> 01:18.165
