to escape

28:11.777 --> 28:13.517
would have been putting
the entire population

28:13.561 --> 28:15.215
of New York City
in imminent danger.

28:15.258 --> 28:18.566
- There are serious
Fourth Amendment issues here.

28:18.609 --> 28:21.090
If we go down this road,
what's next?

28:21.134 --> 28:22.439
Police state?

28:22.483 --> 28:24.659
A mandatory universal
DNA database?

28:24.703 --> 28:26.052
- I see your point.

28:26.095 --> 28:28.750
Mr. Stone, do you have
any other evidence

28:28.794 --> 28:31.013
linking Mr. Noone
to these crimes?

28:31.057 --> 28:32.536
- Yes, Your Honor.

28:32.580 --> 28:33.842
The last victim made a positive
voice identification.

28:33.886 --> 28:36.323
- And that is also tainted.

28:36.366 --> 28:38.238
- I have to agree.

28:38.281 --> 28:39.892
As all the evidence in the case

28:39.935 --> 28:41.850
is fruit of the poisonous tree,

28:41.894 --> 28:44.374
I grant the motion to dismiss.

28:44.418 --> 28:46.420
- Your Honor, this monster

28:46.463 --> 28:49.075
is guilty of 23 rapes.

28:49.118 --> 28:50.467
You dismiss now, we lose

28:50.511 --> 28:52.252
any chance of justice
for those victims.

28:52.295 --> 28:53.775
- I feel your pain, Mr. Stone,

28:53.819 --> 28:55.472
but the evidence
doesn't support

28:55.516 --> 28:56.996
the pending indictment.

28:57.039 --> 28:59.302
I am putting the case over
for a new indictment.

28:59.346 --> 29:03.132
In the mean time, Mr. Noone,
you're free to go.

29:15.405 --> 29:18.495
- Your father would have
done better.

29:30.638 --> 29:31.944
- Hey.

29:31.987 --> 29:32.945
- Hey, thank you
for meeting me.

29:32.988 --> 29:34.250
- Yeah, of course.

29:34.294 --> 29:38.124
I was, uh--I was surprised
that you called.

29:38.167 --> 29:41.954
- My uncle hasn't
called me back.

29:43.216 --> 29:46.175
- What do you think that means?

29:47.220 --> 29:50.005
- DNA doesn't lie, does it?

29:54.270 --> 29:55.881
Oh, God.

29:55.924 --> 29:58.187
Oh, my God.

29:58.231 --> 30:00.668
He used to pick me up
from school,

30:00.711 --> 30:01.669
take me to the park.

30:01.712 --> 30:04.237
How is this possible?

30:08.763 --> 30:11.157
- Amy...

30:11.200 --> 30:14.595
is--is there anything else

30:14.638 --> 30:17.467
that you can tell me
about your uncle?

30:17.511 --> 30:18.904
Anything at all.

30:18.947 --> 30:21.515
- I...

30:23.125 --> 30:26.607
He stayed with us
for a few months.

30:26.650 --> 30:28.783
I was six.

30:28.827 --> 30:32.613
He would wake up in the middle
of the night screaming...

30:34.006 --> 30:36.704
"I can't listen, make it stop!"

30:38.053 --> 30:41.535
Years later, my mom told me
about her and Edgar's parents.

30:41.578 --> 30:42.797
They were alcoholics.

30:42.841 --> 30:46.148
They were always fighting
and...

30:46.192 --> 30:48.237
some nights my grandfather

30:48.281 --> 30:51.197
would lock my mother
and Edgar in their room.

30:51.240 --> 30:54.896
Told them not to make a sound.

30:54.940 --> 30:57.638
- What happened
on those nights?

30:58.900 --> 31:01.163
- She said that...

31:01.207 --> 31:03.774
my grandfather
did horrible things

31:03.818 --> 31:07.082
to my grandmother.

31:07.126 --> 31:09.693
I think he raped her.

31:11.695 --> 31:15.656
- And he made your mother
and Edgar listen, didn't he?

31:25.361 --> 31:27.363
- So my father was tortured
by a man

31:27.407 --> 31:29.278
who was tortured
by his own father?

31:29.322 --> 31:30.149
- Uh-huh.

31:30.192 --> 31:32.107
Probably too little too late.

31:32.151 --> 31:33.674
- Maybe not.

31:33.717 --> 31:36.242
Noone sent over a dozen
"Dear Ben" letters.

31:36.285 --> 31:38.635
They were taunting.
They were full of detail.

31:38.679 --> 31:40.072
- He--he wanted to be caught.

31:40.115 --> 31:42.683
- Yeah, or he wanted
to confess...

31:42.726 --> 31:45.164
to Ben Stone.

31:45.207 --> 31:46.687
See, he saw him
as a father figure.

31:46.730 --> 31:47.906
Look.

31:47.949 --> 31:50.691
He even sent him
a Father's Day card.

31:55.130 --> 31:57.437
- Okay, um...

31:57.480 --> 31:58.960
we gotta find a way
to get this guy back

31:59.004 --> 32:01.745
in the interrogation room.

32:05.010 --> 32:07.664
- You arrested him for driving
on a suspended license?

32:07.708 --> 32:08.970
- An old guy?

32:09.014 --> 32:10.841
Who knew he had
unpaid speeding tickets?

32:10.885 --> 32:12.800
- He hasn't asked
for a lawyer?

32:12.843 --> 32:14.715
- Not yet.

32:14.758 --> 32:16.151
- And he'll talk to us?

32:16.195 --> 32:19.676
- He'll talk to my father.

32:21.896 --> 32:25.204
- "Dear Ben, I was thinking
about you last night.

32:25.247 --> 32:26.248
Wondering about Mary."

32:26.292 --> 32:27.858
- Mary Harris.

32:27.902 --> 32:29.991
Infinity's 22nd victim.

32:30.035 --> 32:31.210
- "Wondering if Mary
would tell you

32:31.253 --> 32:32.254
"what I did to her.

32:32.298 --> 32:33.908
"What I made her say.

32:33.952 --> 32:35.431
"If she would get
the details right

32:35.475 --> 32:36.955
"or if she would leave out
the interesting parts

32:36.998 --> 32:38.304
because she was ashamed."

32:38.347 --> 32:40.523
- Infinity had a way
with words.

32:40.567 --> 32:43.700
- That's probably what made him
interesting to Ben Stone.

32:43.744 --> 32:44.745
- Yeah.

32:44.788 --> 32:46.877
My father studied him.

32:46.921 --> 32:49.532
He read and reread the letters,

32:49.576 --> 32:52.927
looking for clues about--
about the crimes.

32:52.971 --> 32:54.233
His life.

32:54.276 --> 32:57.323
About his traumatic childhood.

32:57.366 --> 32:59.194
- What do you mean?

32:59.238 --> 33:01.980
- As a boy,
Infinity was forced to listen

33:02.023 --> 33:05.157
while his father
raped his mother.

33:06.462 --> 33:09.422
- Explains the pathology,
but...

33:09.465 --> 33:12.120
I don't think any of that
was in the books.

33:12.164 --> 33:14.383
- And--and Ben Stone knew that?

33:14.427 --> 33:16.385
- Oh, my father was obsessed.

33:16.429 --> 33:18.083
I mean, he kept everything.

33:18.126 --> 33:19.910
I mean, look,
letter after letter.

33:19.954 --> 33:23.610
Infinity even sent him
a Father's Day card one year.

33:25.699 --> 33:27.875
Look.

33:29.268 --> 33:32.227
- "Dear Ben,
happy Father's Day."

33:32.271 --> 33:35.578
Signed with
the infinity symbol.

33:45.023 --> 33:47.329
Take a look.

33:48.852 --> 33:50.724
- Ben Stone kept this?

33:50.767 --> 33:53.248
- Yeah, he did.

33:53.292 --> 33:54.771
He kept it in an evidence file

33:54.815 --> 33:56.730
so it wouldn't get smudged
or torn.

33:59.689 --> 34:03.606
- Of course, the idiot,
he sent a card with golf clubs.

34:05.434 --> 34:08.568
My father never played a game
of golf in his life.

34:12.659 --> 34:14.443
- Infinity couldn't
have known that--

34:14.487 --> 34:15.705
- Right.

34:15.749 --> 34:18.273
Because he knew nothing
about my father.

34:18.317 --> 34:19.535
- They had a relationship.

34:19.579 --> 34:22.016
- There was no relationship.

34:22.060 --> 34:25.150
- All those hours Ben Stone
spent on the case?

34:25.193 --> 34:26.716
He spent more time
with Infinity

34:26.760 --> 34:28.457
than he did
with his own family!

34:28.501 --> 34:31.460
- Ben Stone cared about
the women who were raped.

34:31.504 --> 34:34.420
He cared about getting justice
for them.

34:34.463 --> 34:35.725
You're a little confused.

34:35.769 --> 34:37.205
- If you think this was
about you,

34:37.249 --> 34:39.120
you're more insane
than I thought.

34:39.164 --> 34:41.557
- No!

34:42.732 --> 34:44.734
That's not true!

34:44.778 --> 34:47.563
I know!

34:54.048 --> 34:56.572
- You know what?

35:08.280 --> 35:11.413
I would wait outside
the DA's office

35:11.457 --> 35:14.982
until the light
in his office went out.

35:15.025 --> 35:18.072
Some nights, he wouldn't even
get in his car

35:18.116 --> 35:20.509
until after midnight.

35:20.553 --> 35:23.164
It was me he cared about.

35:23.208 --> 35:25.123
Not you.

35:27.777 --> 35:30.040
Me!

35:30.084 --> 35:33.305
It was me he loved!

36:01.811 --> 36:05.424
- He's going to spend
the rest of his life in prison.

36:07.121 --> 36:09.950
Your father
would be proud, Peter.

36:12.257 --> 36:14.433
- I, uh...

36:14.476 --> 36:17.479
I found this
in my father's notes.

36:18.611 --> 36:21.048
Uh, "Peter's game today.

36:21.091 --> 36:23.703
Don't be late.
He's the starting pitcher."

36:25.487 --> 36:26.836
I was in junior high.

36:26.880 --> 36:29.230
It was the first game
of the season.

36:29.274 --> 36:31.406
He never showed.

36:31.450 --> 36:34.627
I hit a homer
in the last inning.

36:37.673 --> 36:40.459
I went home and, uh...

36:40.502 --> 36:42.548
I could tell he wanted to talk,
but I was so angry

36:42.591 --> 36:45.551
I just went to my room.

36:47.030 --> 36:51.034
I'll never forget
the disappointment in his eyes.

36:51.078 --> 36:53.776
- You were a teenager.

36:53.820 --> 36:54.647
- Yeah.

36:54.690 --> 36:56.823
The next day he wrote this:

36:56.866 --> 36:58.520
Uh...

36:58.564 --> 37:01.001
"Peter's team won.

37:01.958 --> 37:05.048
Maybe he'll
forgive me someday."

37:07.486 --> 37:10.271
We never talked
about that game.

37:10.315 --> 37:12.795
It was September '93.

37:17.800 --> 37:19.976
Turns out...

37:20.020 --> 37:23.197
Infinity had struck again
the night before.

37:29.856 --> 37:31.901
- Peter.

37:37.690 --> 37:40.432
It's time to forgive him.

37:51.225 --> 37:53.314
- Yeah.

38:04.369 --> 38:07.372
- Thank you, Lucy.

38:09.504 --> 38:11.201
- Why are you home early?

38:11.245 --> 38:14.117
- I thought we'd spend
a little time together.

38:14.161 --> 38:16.555
- I want Lucy.

38:18.600 --> 38:20.863
Okay, so, uh...

38:20.907 --> 38:22.952
Noah, we all get
in bad moods sometimes,

38:22.996 --> 38:24.563
and that's okay.

38:24.606 --> 38:27.348
And sometimes
it's not about Lucy

38:27.392 --> 38:30.873
or olives or homework.

38:30.917 --> 38:32.222
Right?

38:32.266 --> 38:35.400
It means that we're upset
about something else.

38:40.405 --> 38:43.582
What's wrong, honey?
You can tell me.

38:46.411 --> 38:49.588
Noah?
Tell me.

38:52.286 --> 38:54.332
- It's Jeremy.

38:54.375 --> 38:57.247
He keeps asking
where my dad is.

38:57.291 --> 38:59.162
I told him he's in heaven.

39:02.427 --> 39:03.906
- That's right, Noah.

39:03.950 --> 39:06.387
He is.

39:06.431 --> 39:08.998
- Did he love me?

39:10.391 --> 39:13.263
- Oh, sweetheart.

39:13.307 --> 39:15.962
Honey, of course he did.

39:16.005 --> 39:18.921
Very, very, very much.

39:20.967 --> 39:22.621
And...

39:22.664 --> 39:24.231
someday, when you get older,

39:24.274 --> 39:28.104
I promise you I'm gonna
tell you all about him.

39:28.148 --> 39:30.368
But for right now, it's just--

39:30.411 --> 39:33.588
it's just Team You and Me.

39:33.632 --> 39:36.591
And I feel...

39:37.549 --> 39:40.943
So very lucky
to be on that team.

39:44.599 --> 39:47.167
- Me too.

39:54.479 --> 39:56.002
- I love you, honey.

39:57.307 --> 39:59.701
One sec.

40:04.706 --> 40:07.056
Peter, hey.
Something about the case?

40:07.100 --> 40:10.320
- Actually, I'm not here
to talk to you.

40:10.364 --> 40:11.974
- Coach!
- Hey.

40:12.018 --> 40:14.107
I thought maybe Noah and me
could play a game of catch.

40:14.150 --> 40:16.414
- Can I play catch?
Please, Mom?

40:16.457 --> 40:18.372
- Uh, sure you can.

40:18.416 --> 40:20.635
There you go.

40:20.679 --> 40:21.941
- Yeah.
- Hey, thanks.

40:21.984 --> 40:23.333
Come on, slugger.
- Let's go!

40:23.377 --> 40:24.465
- Shoes.
- Hey, grab your coat!

40:24.509 --> 40:26.162
- And coat.
Here you go.

40:26.206 --> 40:28.077
All right, come on, come on.
Get those shoes on.

40:28.121 --> 40:29.470
- Go, go, go.
- Yeah, that'll work.

40:29.514 --> 40:30.906
That'll work.
Come on, big guy.

40:30.950 --> 40:32.647
Nice one.
All right, put these on.

40:32.691 --> 40:33.648
All right, you ready?

40:33.692 --> 40:36.042
- Let's go.

40:37.173 --> 40:38.610
- Thank you.

40:38.653 --> 40:41.221
Thank you.
